her education today, and concludes with a stirring plea for the kind of education that has, since the founding of the nation, cultivated individual freedom, promulgated civic virtue, and instilled hope for the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEducationxPhilosophy. 0aEducation, HigherxAims and objectives. 0aEducation, Humanistic. 7aEDUCATION / Aims & Objectives.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311067250340uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030020655540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300206555423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300206555/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles